I've been self-publishing since 2012, and have had 150+ rejections from publishers over the last decade.

Now in 2022 my books will be available in Barnes & Noble, and other locations across Canada and the US.

This is surreal.

I ugly-cried as soon as this video ended LOL

I saw a Gary Vee quote where he said this is a 4 quarter game, and at the age of 46, he feels like he's in the 2nd quarter.

If you've been working on a project and you're not getting the results you want, if you feel like it's taking too long ... keep working. Keep trying new things. DEFINITELY keep knocking on new doors, because to succeed, only one has to open.

Apologies for the self indulgence, I just wanted to share with Imgurians.

Love you guys. xox 

PS: I didn't film this myself so technically it's not a selfie, I hope I didn't break the iron-clad 'no selfie rule' at Imgur :P

PPS: I'm fully prepared for the 'girls showing object with her face next to it' meme, so have at it LOL

PPPS: I won't post a book description or any other crap on here, but if you want to see the cover close-up (Isaac Escorza IS F'ING AMAZING) or read the book summary, you can click here

